						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up before the temple of Rāmaliṅgēśvara.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1093, Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land and a lamp-stand made for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Mūlasthāna Rāmēśvara Mahādēva of Siripuram by Mallināyaka, son of Brammi-Nāyaka, for the merit of his parents.</p>						

						</summary>
